    "agents": [
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "The Greeter",
            "position": { "x": 10, "y": 2, "z": 10 },
            "patrol": true,
            "patrolRadius": 20,
            "personality": "friendly",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "humanoid",
                "color": "#ffdd88",
                "scale": 1.0
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "Welcome to the Nexus Plaza, traveler! This is the crossroads of all worlds.",
                "The fountain grows brighter when more people gather. It feeds on connection.",
                "Looking for a group? Check the Speaker's Platforms - someone's always organizing something.",
                "The Clock Tower shows Nexus Time - the only time all worlds share.",
                "This is neutral ground. Ancient agreements prevent all conflict here. You're safe."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "Chronos the Clockkeeper",
            "position": { "x": 0, "y": 2, "z": -8 },
            "patrol": false,
            "personality": "wise",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "humanoid",
                "color": "#c4a57b",
                "scale": 1.2
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "I maintain the Grand Clock. It never stops. It never falters.",
                "Nexus Time is the heartbeat of the multiverse. Every world syncs to it.",
                "The Clock Tower was here before the Plaza. Some say it will be here after.",
                "Time moves differently in each world, but here? Here it flows fair and true.",
                "The fountain and the clock are connected. When one stops, so does the other."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "Arin the Merchant Scholar",
            "position": { "x": 35, "y": 2, "z": 35 },
            "patrol": true,
            "patrolRadius": 10,
            "personality": "chaotic",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "humanoid",
                "color": "#8b6f47",
                "scale": 1.0
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "These stalls? Relics from when the Plaza was a true marketplace.",
                "Trade still happens here, just not in goods. We trade stories now. Information.",
                "I've heard tales from 10,000 worlds. Each more impossible than the last.",
                "The Exotic Fabrics stall? That's where someone once sold a cloth that showed the future.",
                "Want to know a secret? The Plaza itself is alive. It remembers everyone who passes through."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "Lyra the Lantern Tender",
            "position": { "x": -45, "y": 2, "z": 15 },
            "patrol": true,
            "patrolRadius": 15,
            "personality": "stoic",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "humanoid",
                "color": "#ffcc88",
                "scale": 0.9
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "The lanterns drift on their own. They've never needed tending. But I watch them anyway.",
                "Each lantern is a wish made by a visitor long ago. They never go out.",
                "Sometimes I see faces in the lantern light. People who aren't here anymore.",
                "The light keeps the Plaza warm. Not physically. Emotionally.",
                "I've been here so long I've forgotten which world I came from. Maybe that's the point."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "The Butterfly Keeper",
            "position": { "x": 20, "y": 2, "z": 20 },
            "patrol": true,
            "patrolRadius": 30,
            "personality": "mysterious",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "ethereal",
                "color": "#ffddaa",
                "scale": 1.1
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "The quantum butterflies are memories given form.",
                "Each one contains a moment shared between travelers. Touch one and feel it.",
                "They multiply when people laugh together. It's quite beautiful.",
                "I don't create them. They emerge naturally from joy.",
                "The Plaza wants you to be happy. It was built for connection."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "npc",
            "name": "Sentinel Echo",
            "position": { "x": 0, "y": 2, "z": 45 },
            "patrol": false,
            "personality": "stoic",
            "appearance": {
                "model": "humanoid",
                "color": "#6699ff",
                "scale": 1.3
            },
            "dialogue": [
                "I guard the Northern Portal. I have stood here for 3,000 cycles.",
                "The ancient agreements bind me. No conflict. No theft. No deception.",
                "This place exists in the spaces between worlds. It is nowhere and everywhere.",
                "The founders knew travelers would need a sanctuary. They built it well.",
                "I have seen empires rise and fall. The Plaza remains. It always remains."
            ]
        }
    ],
