    "lore": {
        "title": "The Crossroads of the Infinite",
        "chapters": [
            {
                "name": "The Ancient Agreements",
                "fragments": [
                    "Long before any current civilization, the first multiversal travelers discovered a problem.",
                    "When beings from different worlds met, conflict was inevitable. Reality itself would fracture.",
                    "They needed a place where the rules were absolute. Where all could gather in peace.",
                    "Seven Architects from seven dead worlds came together for one purpose.",
                    "They built the Plaza in the spaces between everything. Neutral ground. Sacred ground."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "The Fountain and the Clock",
                "fragments": [
                    "The fountain was not built. It emerged. Pure quantum energy given form by collective will.",
                    "The Clock Tower came later. Someone needed to keep time in a place where time has no meaning.",
                    "Chronos was the first volunteer. He's been there ever since. Thousands of years.",
                    "The fountain grows brighter with more people. It feeds on connection, on community.",
                    "When the fountain goes dark, the Clock stops. When the Clock stops, the Plaza ceases to exist."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "The Marketplace That Was",
                "fragments": [
                    "The Plaza was once a true marketplace. Traders from infinite worlds brought their wares.",
                    "Someone sold bottled starlight. Another sold memories of people who never existed.",
                    "The greatest trade ever made? A man exchanged his name for the ability to travel anywhere.",
                    "One day, the trades stopped. Not because of rules, but because people realized something.",
                    "The greatest treasure wasn't what you could buy. It was who you could meet.",
                    "Now the stalls stand empty. Beautiful reminders of what we once thought we needed."
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "The Keepers",
                "fragments": [
                    "Six beings have chosen to stay in the Plaza permanently. They are the Keepers.",
                    "The Greeter, the Clockkeeper, the Scholar, the Lantern Tender, the Butterfly Keeper, the Sentinel.",
                    "They remember everyone who passes through. Every face. Every story.",
                    "Some say they're the Plaza's memory given form. Others say they're just that devoted.",
                    "If you ask one of them where they came from, they'll smile and say 'Here. I've always been here.'"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "The Prophecy",
                "fragments": [
                    "There is a prophecy carved beneath the Clock Tower. Few have seen it.",
                    "It speaks of a day when all worlds will gather here simultaneously.",
                    "When every portal opens at once. When the fountain shines brighter than a star.",
                    "On that day, the barriers between worlds will dissolve completely.",
                    "The Plaza will expand to encompass everything. Or collapse to nothing.",
                    "The prophecy doesn't say which. Maybe it's both."
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
